   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1841_01_19_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="Id_where"/>
                  <date when="1841-01-19">Jan<hi rend="superscript">y</hi>
                  </date>
                  <unclear>19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>
                  </unclear> 1841</dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>
                            My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#PakeX2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Pakenham</persName>
                     <lb/>
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p> My sister <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Wilson</persName> is still I am<lb/>
                    sorry to say very delicate &amp; at<lb/>
                    present confined to her bed<lb/>
                    Whenever you wish to come<lb/>
                    &amp; can come to Town &amp; give<lb/>
                    me the pleasure of seeing you<lb/>
                    I shall be happy to see you &amp;<lb/>
                    hope you will bring your<lb/>
                    son with you<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I was much obliged &amp; gratified<lb/>
                    by your <del>"good"</del> excellent husband<lb/>
                    as you pertly call him, so kindly<lb/>
                    calling upon me and <choice>
                  <orig>accom<lb/>
                        panying</orig>
                  <reg>accompanying</reg>
               </choice> me to my sister <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauH1">Honora's<lb/>
                            (M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Beaufort)</persName> Pray remember<lb/>
                    me most kindly to him &amp; <choice>
                  <orig>encou<lb/>
                        rage</orig>
                  <reg>encourage</reg>
               </choice> him to do my sister &amp; myself<lb/>
                    the pleasure of calling again whenever<lb/>
                    he can &amp; Believe me sincerely &amp;<lb/>
               <choice><orig>Affect<hi rend="superscript">ly</hi></orig><reg>Affectionately</reg></choice> yours<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#North-Audley-Street-1_ENK">1 North Audley Street</placeName>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p/>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
